Okay, get out of here
before you make me cry.

90
00:05:14,484 --> 00:05:15,694
Bonne chance!

91
00:05:20,449 --> 00:05:23,160
Big smile!
Great! Thank you!

92
00:05:23,243 --> 00:05:26,913
# The waves keep on crashin'
on me for some reason #

93
00:05:26,955 --> 00:05:28,123
Good to see you.

94
00:05:28,206 --> 00:05:29,958
Secretary Hennings,

95
00:05:30,042 --> 00:05:31,710
do you have a moment
for a few questions?

96
00:05:31,793 --> 00:05:34,046
Andrew, are you excited
about the show?

97
00:05:34,129 --> 00:05:36,131
Uh, of course,
I'm very excited.

98
00:05:36,214 --> 00:05:38,258
Did you get to
see the models?

99
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:39,676
The models? Why, uh...

100
00:05:39,760 --> 00:05:41,803
Please tell me
he has a flaw somewhere.

101
00:05:41,887 --> 00:05:45,265
He asked me to go to
Ireland for Christmas.

102
00:05:45,307 --> 00:05:48,352
He's gonna ask you
a lot more than that.

103
00:05:48,435 --> 00:05:50,479
...You think so?
...Mm-hmm.

104
00:05:50,562 --> 00:05:52,022
...Hey, let's go!
...Let's do this!

105
00:05:52,105 --> 00:05:54,816
All right, we gotta go.
Places, everyone!

106
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:56,485
...Come on, let's go, line up.
...Have a good show.

107
00:05:56,568 --> 00:05:59,488
Okay, no smiles,
no smiles, just smirks!

108
00:05:59,571 --> 00:06:02,157
# Keep on dancin' #

109
00:06:05,202 --> 00:06:08,747
# You hold me like you should,
so I'm gonna keep on dancin' #

110
00:06:08,830 --> 00:06:12,584
# Keep on dancin' #

111
00:06:19,675 --> 00:06:20,634
Ohh!

112
00:06:20,717 --> 00:06:22,469
Honey!

113
00:06:22,511 --> 00:06:24,304
...[Shrieks]
...Oh, congratulations.

114
00:06:24,346 --> 00:06:27,140
You're amazing.
Those flowers were insane.

115
00:06:27,224 --> 00:06:29,017
Oh, well, I just want
this day to be perfect.

116
00:06:29,101 --> 00:06:30,686
[Sighs] Oh, God, honey,
what if they hate me?

117
00:06:30,769 --> 00:06:32,813
Oh, they're critics, Mel.
They hate themselves.

118
00:06:32,896 --> 00:06:34,147
That's easy for you to say.

119
00:06:34,231 --> 00:06:35,857
I wasn't born with
that thick Hennings skin.

120
00:06:35,941 --> 00:06:38,819
No, you weren't, and that
is what I love about you.

121
00:06:38,860 --> 00:06:40,279
Mmm.

122
00:06:40,362 --> 00:06:42,281
Ah, honey, I'm sorry, I got
a meeting in the Bronx.

123
00:06:42,364 --> 00:06:44,783
But you go and enjoy, and
I'll see you later. Okay?

124
00:06:44,866 --> 00:06:47,452
Oh, and, hey, we've got that
thing tonight at Lincoln Center.

125
00:06:47,536 --> 00:06:49,121
What thing?

126
00:06:49,204 --> 00:06:50,747
Fund-raiser thing.

127
00:06:50,831 --> 00:06:54,167
[Sighs] Right, the thing...
with your mother.

128
00:06:54,251 --> 00:06:55,544
That's tonight.

129
00:06:55,627 --> 00:06:56,837
I'm afraid so.

130
00:06:56,920 --> 00:06:57,879
Okay.

131
00:06:57,921 --> 00:07:00,382
I am so proud of you.

132
00:07:00,424 --> 00:07:02,843
Thank you.

133
00:07:02,884 --> 00:07:03,969
...Okay?
...I love you.

134
00:07:04,052 --> 00:07:05,679
I love you, too.
Congratulations.

135
00:07:09,433 --> 00:07:11,184
[Horn honks]

136
00:07:25,115 --> 00:07:26,658
His meeting's running
a little late.

137
00:07:26,742 --> 00:07:29,411
He told me to take you inside
so you wouldn't have to wait.

138
00:07:29,494 --> 00:07:30,746
Where are we?

139
00:07:32,331 --> 00:07:34,916
[Horn honks]

140
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:37,002
...I'm so tired, Jimmy.
...Yeah.

141
00:07:37,085 --> 00:07:38,420
I've just had it.

142
00:07:38,503 --> 00:07:41,882
Well... he shouldn't be
too long.

143
00:07:41,924 --> 00:07:44,760
Miss Carmichael,
won't you come in?

144
00:07:53,602 --> 00:07:56,688
So... have you made a decision?

145
00:07:56,772 --> 00:07:57,940
A-bout what?

146
00:07:58,023 --> 00:07:59,274
Ireland.

147
00:07:59,358 --> 00:08:03,403
Ireland, honey, [Scoffs]
that's four months from now.

148
00:08:03,779 --> 00:08:05,530
I was thinking maybe
2... 300 guests, tops.

149
00:08:05,530 --> 00:08:07,741
I was thinking maybe
2... 300 guests, tops.

150
00:08:07,824 --> 00:08:09,284
For Christmas?

151
00:08:09,368 --> 00:08:12,913
Andrew, are you on
some sort of medication?

152
00:08:12,955 --> 00:08:16,583
What's going on?
Where are we?

153
00:08:35,644 --> 00:08:39,147
[Gasps] Oh, my God.

154
00:08:39,231 --> 00:08:42,442
O-Oh, my God.

155
00:08:47,239 --> 00:08:49,825
Oh, my God.

156
00:08:49,908 --> 00:08:52,286
Melanie Carmichael...

157
00:08:52,327 --> 00:08:54,454
will you marry me?

158
00:08:56,248 --> 00:08:57,666
Are you sure?

159
00:08:57,749 --> 00:09:00,335
I mean, a-a-are
you really sure?

160
00:09:00,419 --> 00:09:02,337
Because if you're not sure, we
could just go back to the car.

161
00:09:02,421 --> 00:09:04,006
...Mel, Mel, Mel, Mel...
...It's only been 8 months.

162
00:09:04,089 --> 00:09:05,882
You know I never do
anything rash.

163
00:09:05,966 --> 00:09:07,926
And I usually never
ask a question

164
00:09:08,010 --> 00:09:09,678
I don't already know
the answer to,

165
00:09:09,761 --> 00:09:14,349
so... at the risk of
being rejected twice,

166
00:09:14,433 --> 00:09:16,351
I'm gonna ask you again.

167
00:09:20,063 --> 00:09:22,190
Will you marry me?

168
00:09:24,484 --> 00:09:26,194
Yes!

169
00:09:26,278 --> 00:09:28,196
Yes! Yes!

170
00:09:28,238 --> 00:09:29,197
[Both laugh]

171
00:09:29,239 --> 00:09:29,906
Yes!

172
00:09:33,910 --> 00:09:35,996
Pick one.

173
00:09:52,262 --> 00:09:53,555
Mayor, just one shot!
One shot!

174
00:09:53,639 --> 00:09:55,098
Can you comment on
the Watson bill?

175
00:09:55,182 --> 00:09:56,600
Over here, Mayor, please!
Over here!

176
00:09:56,683 --> 00:09:59,227
Thank you.
Where is he?

177
00:09:59,311 --> 00:10:00,520
He's running late.

178
00:10:00,604 --> 00:10:02,272
No doubt thanks to
that Carbuncle girl.

179
00:10:02,356 --> 00:10:03,732
Carmichael...
designer, Southern.

180
00:10:03,815 --> 00:10:04,983
Right, whatever.

181
00:10:05,067 --> 00:10:06,693
Right here, Mayor!

182
00:10:06,777 --> 00:10:08,278
...Please, Mayor!
...Miss Mayor, over here!

183
00:10:08,362 --> 00:10:09,738
Your Honor,
how do you answer those

184
00:10:09,821 --> 00:10:11,698
who are opposed to
the street-improvement project

185
00:10:11,740 --> 00:10:13,325
you put before
the city council today?

186
00:10:13,408 --> 00:10:16,244
I suggest they take a drive on
some of the streets in Brooklyn.

187
00:10:16,328 --> 00:10:19,206
Maybe they'll disappear
into a pothole.

188
00:10:19,247 --> 00:10:21,833
Your son's relationship
with Melanie Carmichael...

189
00:10:21,917 --> 00:10:24,419
sources say they're engaged.
Do you have a comment?

190
00:10:24,503 --> 00:10:28,382
Trust me, if my son were
engaged, I'd have a comment.

191
00:10:30,759 --> 00:10:32,427
I thought you were tired.

192
00:10:32,511 --> 00:10:35,180
Jimmy, can you excuse us
for a second?

193
00:10:35,264 --> 00:10:36,348
[Chuckles]

194
00:10:38,433 --> 00:10:40,018
I've been planning
this for weeks.

195
00:10:40,102 --> 00:10:43,105
I knew your show would be great,
and tonight is perfect.

196
00:10:43,188 --> 00:10:46,149
Oh, God, I can't wait to see
the look on my mother's face.

197
00:10:46,233 --> 00:10:48,235
Come on,
let's call your parents.

198
00:10:48,318 --> 00:10:49,444
No!

199
00:10:49,528 --> 00:10:50,821
l-I mean...
[Chuckles nervously]

200
00:10:50,904 --> 00:10:52,698
n-not right this second.

201
00:10:54,032 --> 00:10:55,075
What I mean is, uh...

202
00:10:55,158 --> 00:10:56,743
Honey, would you
mind terribly

203
00:10:56,827 --> 00:10:59,288
if we just kept this to
ourselves for a few days?

204
00:10:59,329 --> 00:11:02,582
Mel, it's gonna come out
sooner or later.

205
00:11:02,624 --> 00:11:04,668
No, l-I know,
I know, but, um,

206
00:11:04,751 --> 00:11:07,170
it's just, I haven't seen
my folks in about 7 years,

207
00:11:07,254 --> 00:11:11,633
and I just feel like I should
probably tell them in person.

208
00:11:11,675 --> 00:11:12,968
Of course.

209
00:11:14,511 --> 00:11:18,640
And, um... l-I think
I should do it alone.

210
00:11:18,724 --> 00:11:21,435
Mel, I'm gonna have to
meet them eventually.

211
00:11:21,476 --> 00:11:24,146
l-I know, I know, and
they will love you...

212
00:11:24,229 --> 00:11:25,314
eventually.

213
00:11:27,899 --> 00:11:29,818
Is it because
I'm a Yankee?

214
00:11:29,860 --> 00:11:32,863
Well, that...
and a Democrat.

215
00:11:37,326 --> 00:11:39,453
Okay... mum's the word.

216
00:11:39,536 --> 00:11:41,913
...No one will know.
...Thank you.

217
00:11:45,500 --> 00:11:48,587
Secretary Hennings,
will you comment...

218
00:11:48,670 --> 00:11:50,589
Secretary Hennings...

219
00:11:50,672 --> 00:11:52,132
Okay. [Laughs]

220
00:11:52,174 --> 00:11:53,550
Hello.

221
00:11:56,678 --> 00:11:58,847
