Sorry, honey,
she just grabbed my hand.

245
00:13:05,664 --> 00:13:06,915
What was I supposed to do?

246
00:13:06,999 --> 00:13:08,417
I know...
we read all about it.

247
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:10,210
...So, did you cry?
...Wouldn't you?

248
00:13:10,294 --> 00:13:12,713
One man for the rest of my life?
I'd bawl my bloody eyes out.

249
00:13:12,754 --> 00:13:15,257
So why don't you meet us?
We're just around the corner.

250
00:13:15,340 --> 00:13:17,759
[Sighs] Can't.

251
00:13:17,801 --> 00:13:20,095
I'm in Alabama.

252
00:13:20,178 --> 00:13:23,890
Oh... my God.

253
00:13:25,684 --> 00:13:26,685
Yeah.

254
00:14:21,156 --> 00:14:23,492
[Birds chirping]

255
00:14:25,827 --> 00:14:27,162
[Barks]

256
00:14:29,331 --> 00:14:31,667
[Barks]

257
00:14:34,002 --> 00:14:38,882
[Barking slowly]

258
00:14:46,223 --> 00:14:48,767
Aw, he's loud,
but he don't bite.

259
00:14:48,850 --> 00:14:50,310
Come on, shut up, hound!

260
00:14:50,394 --> 00:14:51,436
Lie down.

261
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:53,689
Go on, stay.

262
00:14:53,772 --> 00:14:56,024
Now, how can I help you?

263
00:14:56,108 --> 00:14:59,194
Well, for starters, you can get
your stubborn ass down here

264
00:14:59,278 --> 00:15:00,696
and give me a divorce.

265
00:15:03,407 --> 00:15:05,701
...[Thud]
...[Groans]

266
00:15:05,784 --> 00:15:07,452
[Sighs] Come on,
Jake, I mean it.

267
00:15:07,536 --> 00:15:08,870
The joke's over.

268
00:15:08,954 --> 00:15:10,831
Let's just finish this.
I've got a plane to catch.

269
00:15:14,334 --> 00:15:16,128
You're shittin' me, right?

270
00:15:16,211 --> 00:15:18,714
You know, I've never actually
understood that expression,

271
00:15:18,797 --> 00:15:20,716
but, no,
I'm not "shitting" you.

272
00:15:20,757 --> 00:15:24,177
Look, it's even got
these idiot-proof tabs

273
00:15:24,219 --> 00:15:25,345
to make it easy.

274
00:15:25,387 --> 00:15:27,598
There's one copy for me,
one copy for you,

275
00:15:27,681 --> 00:15:29,391
and one copy
for the lawyers.

276
00:15:29,474 --> 00:15:32,519
[Exhales sharply]

277
00:15:34,771 --> 00:15:36,023
What? Speak!

278
00:15:36,064 --> 00:15:37,024
[Slow barking resumes]

279
00:15:37,065 --> 00:15:40,694
You show up here
after 7 years

280
00:15:40,736 --> 00:15:44,197
without so much as a "Hey,
there, Jake, remember me...

281
00:15:44,239 --> 00:15:46,408
your wife?"

282
00:15:46,491 --> 00:15:49,536
Or a "Hi, honey.
Lookin' good.

283
00:15:49,620 --> 00:15:51,580
How's the family?"

284
00:15:51,663 --> 00:15:53,498
You expect me to tell you
you look good?

285
00:15:53,582 --> 00:15:55,918
Did they run out of soap down at
the Piggly Wiggly since I left?

286
00:15:56,001 --> 00:15:57,044
[Slow barking continues]

287
00:15:57,127 --> 00:15:59,838
They laugh at that up north
or wherever it is you been?

288
00:15:59,922 --> 00:16:01,548
You knew where I was.

289
00:16:01,632 --> 00:16:03,926
And don't even pretend you spent
all this time missing me.

290
00:16:04,009 --> 00:16:05,761
Oh, I missed you,
all right.

291
00:16:05,844 --> 00:16:08,513
But at this range,
my aim is bound to improve.

292
00:16:08,597 --> 00:16:10,557
Is that a threat?

293
00:16:10,641 --> 00:16:13,060
I've got a lawyer
who charges $350 an hour.

294
00:16:13,101 --> 00:16:15,896
He billed me every time
you sent these papers back.

295
00:16:15,938 --> 00:16:17,940
Well, I'm glad to see
you finally got the message.

296
00:16:17,981 --> 00:16:19,858
...Shut up, Bear!
...Shut up, Bryant!

297
00:16:19,942 --> 00:16:22,736
[Barks, groans]

298
00:16:22,778 --> 00:16:25,614
What happened to Bear?

299
00:16:25,697 --> 00:16:28,200
He died.

300
00:16:28,283 --> 00:16:29,868
You weren't here.

301
00:16:31,286 --> 00:16:32,704
What are you doing?!

302
00:16:32,788 --> 00:16:34,164
Leavin'. You done it.

303
00:16:34,247 --> 00:16:36,583
You should recognize
the gesture.

304
00:16:36,625 --> 00:16:39,920
Could we just try to keep this
as civilized as possible?

305
00:16:39,962 --> 00:16:42,547
Please sign these papers
so I can go home.

306
00:16:42,631 --> 00:16:44,258
What do you know from home?

307
00:16:44,341 --> 00:16:47,302
Hell, I bet your folks don't
even know you're in town.

308
00:16:47,344 --> 00:16:48,929
That's my business.

309
00:16:49,012 --> 00:16:52,140
Honey, those people are
the only family you got.

310
00:16:52,224 --> 00:16:53,558
Don't you "honey" me,
honey!

311
00:16:53,642 --> 00:16:56,770
Get your butt back in that car,
you drive over and see 'em,

312
00:16:56,853 --> 00:16:59,439
and then maybe we'll talk.

313
00:16:59,523 --> 00:17:00,649
[Screen door slams]

314
00:17:00,732 --> 00:17:03,527
Jake! You dumb, stubborn,
redneck hick!

315
00:17:03,610 --> 00:17:05,862
The only reason you
won't sign these papers

316
00:17:05,946 --> 00:17:07,155
is 'cause I want you to!

317
00:17:07,239 --> 00:17:09,283
Wrong! The only reason
I ain't signin'

318
00:17:09,366 --> 00:17:13,453
is 'cause you've turned into
some hoity-toity Yankee bitch,

319
00:17:13,537 --> 00:17:17,082
and I'd like nothin' better
right now than to piss you off!

320
00:17:20,127 --> 00:17:23,213
[Grumbling]

321
00:17:27,551 --> 00:17:29,136
Unh!

322
00:17:30,846 --> 00:17:33,765
What are you doin' with
Mose Plydell's plane anyhow?!

323
00:17:33,849 --> 00:17:34,975
That's my business!

324
00:17:35,017 --> 00:17:37,144
...Fine!
...Fine!

325
00:17:42,524 --> 00:17:44,651
[Door locks]

326
00:17:51,408 --> 00:17:54,411
[Groans]
Divorce, my ass.

327
00:18:04,713 --> 00:18:06,506
[Groans softly]

328
00:18:10,802 --> 00:18:12,304
Hey, genius...

329
00:18:12,387 --> 00:18:14,848
[Sighs]

330
00:18:14,890 --> 00:18:17,100
Next time you lock somebody out,

331
00:18:17,184 --> 00:18:20,187
make sure they don't know
where the spare key's hidden.

332
00:18:20,228 --> 00:18:24,191
Well, see, that's the thing
about Hide-A-Keys...

333
00:18:24,232 --> 00:18:28,195
it'd be nice if your wife
told you where it was!

334
00:18:28,236 --> 00:18:30,364
I'm not your wife, Jake.

335
00:18:30,405 --> 00:18:33,283
I'm just the first girl

336
00:18:33,367 --> 00:18:35,369
that climbed
in the back of your truck.

337
00:18:37,079 --> 00:18:41,041
But you're right...
I have changed.

338
00:18:41,083 --> 00:18:43,669
I don't even know
that girl anymore.

339
00:18:43,752 --> 00:18:49,049
Well, then...
allow me to remind you.

340
00:18:56,473 --> 00:18:58,517
[Door slams]

341
00:18:58,600 --> 00:19:03,313
"Born into one of the wealthiest
families of Greenville, Alabama,

342
00:19:03,397 --> 00:19:07,067
her daddy's in cotton and
all that that implies."

343
00:19:07,109 --> 00:19:10,445
There's no listing for an
Earl Carmichael in Greenville.

344
00:19:10,529 --> 00:19:11,780
How about her local high school?

345
00:19:11,863 --> 00:19:15,075
No record of a Melanie
Carmichael attending... ever.

346
00:19:15,158 --> 00:19:19,121
Jesus! Whatever happened
to responsible journalism?

347
00:19:22,457 --> 00:19:24,793
There's something
wrong here.

348
00:19:24,876 --> 00:19:27,629
Why would my son
do this to me?

349
00:19:27,713 --> 00:19:29,673
Maybe he, um, loves her.

350
00:19:29,756 --> 00:19:30,799
Oh, please!

351
00:19:30,882 --> 00:19:32,801
This is classic rebound.

352
00:19:32,884 --> 00:19:35,470
He's still wounded from...
who was his last girlfriend?

353
00:19:35,554 --> 00:19:38,265
Whitney Truesdale,
lawyer, San Francisco.

354
00:19:38,348 --> 00:19:40,684
Yeah, well, there was
a match made in Heaven...

355
00:19:40,767 --> 00:19:45,022
society, political family,
California...

356
00:19:45,105 --> 00:19:47,441
all those electoral votes.

357
00:19:47,524 --> 00:19:49,776
Get Andrew on the phone.

358
00:19:49,860 --> 00:19:53,322
Since we have a small window
for the Secretary of Housing,

359
00:19:53,405 --> 00:19:55,907
please hold your questions
until after the presentation.

360
00:19:55,991 --> 00:19:57,451
Gentlemen.

361
00:19:57,492 --> 00:19:59,161
Did you see the look
on my mom's face?

362
00:19:59,244 --> 00:20:00,829
I thought her head
was going to explode.

363
00:20:00,912 --> 00:20:02,205
Yeah, what did she say?

364
00:20:02,289 --> 00:20:04,166
That I should date women
like Melanie, not marry them.

365
00:20:04,249 --> 00:20:06,793
...That's harsh.
...That's Mom.

366
00:20:06,877 --> 00:20:08,378
...Thank you.
...Thanks a lot.

367
00:20:08,462 --> 00:20:10,213
We hope to have
the Bronx Children's Hospital

368
00:20:10,297 --> 00:20:12,174
...open by fall 2003.
...[Cellphone ringing]

369
00:20:12,257 --> 00:20:14,593
Oh, speak of the devil.
Hello?

370
00:20:14,676 --> 00:20:17,346
So, have you two lovebirds
set a date?

371
00:20:17,429 --> 00:20:18,889
I'm pleading the Fifth.

372
00:20:18,972 --> 00:20:21,183
Okay, fine, just try to keep
your secrets. I dare you.

373
00:20:21,266 --> 00:20:23,185
Oh, at least you sound like
you're in a better mood.

374
00:20:23,268 --> 00:20:25,062
My approval rating
went up 2 points.

375
00:20:25,145 --> 00:20:27,689
It seems the public likes
being reminded I am a mother.

376
00:20:27,773 --> 00:20:29,191
God, always running for office.

377
00:20:29,274 --> 00:20:32,486
I'm only thinking of you.
Say, um...

378
00:20:32,527 --> 00:20:35,155
do you happen to have
the Carmichaels' number

379
00:20:35,197 --> 00:20:37,491
down there in Greenville?

380
00:20:37,532 --> 00:20:40,327
I thought perhaps
I should introduce myself.

381
00:20:40,410 --> 00:20:42,496
I would like to meet them first,
if you don't mind.

382
00:20:42,579 --> 00:20:45,332
You do realize the press
is going to be all over this.

383
00:20:45,415 --> 00:20:47,167
Happy couples don't sell.

384
00:20:47,209 --> 00:20:50,754
So if there are any skeletons
in her closet, Andrew,

385
00:20:50,837 --> 00:20:52,714
we need to know about them.

386
00:20:52,798 --> 00:20:55,801
[Indistinct talking
on police radio]

387
00:20:57,261 --> 00:20:58,887
You make clothes, right?

388
00:20:58,971 --> 00:21:01,723
I design them.
There's a big difference.

389
00:21:01,807 --> 00:21:04,226
Did you design anything
with stripes?

390
00:21:04,268 --> 00:21:07,187
...[Knock on door]
...You called the sheriff?!

391
00:21:07,229 --> 00:21:10,857
You know that old bastard
hates me!

392
00:21:10,899 --> 00:21:12,484
For good reason!

393
00:21:12,567 --> 00:21:16,989
Well, hell's bells, if
it ain't Felony Melanie.

394
00:21:17,072 --> 00:21:19,157
Wade!

395
00:21:19,241 --> 00:21:23,370
Hot damn, girl,
do we miss you around here!

396
00:21:23,453 --> 00:21:25,872
Hey, I think I saw poor, old
Fuzz just the other day.

397
00:21:25,914 --> 00:21:27,582
Oh, God,
you had to bring that up.

398
00:21:27,666 --> 00:21:29,376
I can't believe
you're the sheriff!

399
00:21:29,418 --> 00:21:31,420
Yep, I get to frisk pretty
little things like you all day

400
00:21:31,461 --> 00:21:33,005
and get paid for it.

401
00:21:33,088 --> 00:21:34,923
Wade, can you try and be
a little more professional?

402
00:21:35,007 --> 00:21:36,508
We got us a crime suspect here.

403
00:21:36,592 --> 00:21:39,678
Now, Melanie, you can't just go
breaking into people's houses.

404
00:21:39,761 --> 00:21:42,764
I didn't break in, Wade.
I used a key...

405
00:21:42,848 --> 00:21:44,016
my key.

406
00:21:46,059 --> 00:21:47,769
Well, it still ain't
your house, darlin'.

407
00:21:47,853 --> 00:21:49,271
I'm gonna have to
escort you out.

408
00:21:49,354 --> 00:21:51,106
Use the cuffs, Wade, please?

409
00:21:51,189 --> 00:21:54,359
If you get him to sign these,
I'll let you run me out of town.

410
00:21:54,443 --> 00:21:55,569
Now, that's none
of your concern.

411
00:21:55,611 --> 00:21:57,195
Well, what do we got here?

412
00:22:00,115 --> 00:22:03,035
...A bill of divorcement?
...Mm-hmm.

413
00:22:03,118 --> 00:22:05,120
Hell, boy, I thought you said
you took care of this.

414
00:22:05,203 --> 00:22:06,455
And I thought I had.

415
00:22:06,538 --> 00:22:07,914
Obviously not.

416
00:22:07,998 --> 00:22:10,250
Well, if you two are still
married, it's her house, too.

417
00:22:10,292 --> 00:22:12,920
This here ain't nothin'
but a domestic dispute.

418
00:22:12,961 --> 00:22:14,755
He didn't hit you, did he?

419
00:22:14,796 --> 00:22:17,799
If he took a swing at you,
I'll take him in right now.

420
00:22:17,841 --> 00:22:19,927
We take that stuff
pretty serious nowadays.

421
00:22:24,306 --> 00:22:27,309
No, Wade,
Jake's never hit me.

422
00:22:27,392 --> 00:22:29,603
You know what?

423
00:22:29,645 --> 00:22:31,980
I don't have a single
childhood memory

424
00:22:32,064 --> 00:22:34,107
that doesn't have
you two in it.

425
00:22:34,149 --> 00:22:37,152
And that includes the night
I lit my ass on fire. Remember?

426
00:22:37,194 --> 00:22:38,111
Wade...

427
00:22:38,195 --> 00:22:41,073
Memory Lane is closed.

428
00:22:41,156 --> 00:22:44,785
Ah, boy, you two got a whole lot
of catchin' up to do...

429
00:22:44,826 --> 00:22:46,745
so I'm just gonna
leave you to it.

430
00:22:46,828 --> 00:22:48,580
Man, I set you up with
your wife. You owe me one!

431
00:22:48,664 --> 00:22:49,957
Why won't you just
sign the papers?!

432
00:22:50,040 --> 00:22:51,458
Hey, there is
nothin' I can do.

433
00:22:51,500 --> 00:22:55,671
The law is the law,
and she has done nothin' wrong.

434
00:22:55,754 --> 00:22:58,257
I suppose shoplifting steaks
at Winn-Dixie's okay.

435
00:22:58,340 --> 00:23:00,968
Oh! Oh! Oh! Oh! Oh!

436
00:23:01,051 --> 00:23:02,636
I took 'em back,
and you know it!

437
00:23:02,719 --> 00:23:06,014
You remember that vandalism out
at the stockyard? Totally her!

438
00:23:06,098 --> 00:23:08,308
Like I could tip a cow
by myself.

439
00:23:08,350 --> 00:23:09,643
Hmm.

440
00:23:09,726 --> 00:23:13,438
Wade... isn't there
some outstanding warrant

441
00:23:13,522 --> 00:23:16,191
for whoever dumped your mama's
tractor in the fishpond?

442
00:23:16,275 --> 00:23:17,276
[Gasps]

443
00:23:17,359 --> 00:23:19,820
[Sighs deeply]

444
00:23:23,282 --> 00:23:25,325
We only have 10 of these, and
it's gonna be gone for good.

445
00:23:25,409 --> 00:23:27,536
So if you are loving
this monster...

446
00:23:27,619 --> 00:23:30,330
...[Snoring]
...[Telephone rings]

447
00:23:30,414 --> 00:23:31,999
We have eight only?

448
00:23:32,040 --> 00:23:34,251
If I knew how to say that in
Italian, I would, but I don't.

449
00:23:34,334 --> 00:23:35,961
Um, if you love this...

450
00:23:36,044 --> 00:23:39,172
9: 15? Honestly.

451
00:23:39,256 --> 00:23:41,174
Who could be callin'
at this hour?

452
00:23:41,883 --> 00:23:43,510
Hello?

453
00:23:43,594 --> 00:23:45,220
Hel-lo?

454
00:23:45,304 --> 00:23:47,347
Melanie: Hey, Mama.

455
00:23:47,431 --> 00:23:49,558
Melanie? Is that you?

456
00:23:49,641 --> 00:23:51,602
Oh, it's so late.
Are you all right?

457
00:23:51,685 --> 00:23:54,646
I, uh... um...

458
00:23:54,730 --> 00:23:56,648
I just thought
I'd surprise you.

459
00:23:56,732 --> 00:24:00,152
Well, this certainly is a fine
surprise, hearing from you...

460
00:24:00,235 --> 00:24:02,738
you know,
being such a busy girl and all.

461
00:24:02,821 --> 00:24:04,489
Of course, I call people

462
00:24:04,573 --> 00:24:07,659
while I'm doin' the dishes
or shellin' peas.

463
00:24:07,743 --> 00:24:10,746
Oprah calls it
"multitasking."

464
00:24:10,829 --> 00:24:13,498
Mama, the call
isn't the surprise.

465
00:24:13,582 --> 00:24:14,666
l-I'm in town.

466
00:24:14,750 --> 00:24:17,044
Oh, Lord, love a duck!
Ha!

467
00:24:17,127 --> 00:24:20,380
Oh, my baby girl
has finally come home.

468
00:24:20,422 --> 00:24:22,090
Earl, she's in town.

469
00:24:22,174 --> 00:24:23,967
Earl: You gonna repeat
everything she says?

470
00:24:24,051 --> 00:24:26,219
...If you are, get off my chair.
...Mama...

471
00:24:26,303 --> 00:24:27,971
I'm just sittin' here, is all.

472
00:24:28,055 --> 00:24:29,389
What happened to the sound?

473
00:24:29,473 --> 00:24:31,975
I turned it down
so I could hear the phone ring.

474
00:24:32,059 --> 00:24:34,227
...Mama!
...What, are you a clairvoyant?

475
00:24:34,311 --> 00:24:36,355
It was so loud,
I couldn't hear myself think.

476
00:24:36,438 --> 00:24:39,691
...Mama...
...They could have heard it
at Joe and Lurlynn's house.

477
00:24:39,775 --> 00:24:41,526
...Hello?
...I only get 3 minutes.

478
00:24:41,610 --> 00:24:44,738
Oh, honey, you didn't need
to call, then. Just come on by.

479
00:24:44,780 --> 00:24:46,907
Uh... well, that's the thing.

480
00:24:46,990 --> 00:24:50,369
I was sorta hoping
Daddy could come get me.

481
00:24:53,455 --> 00:24:56,291
Earl: So, what put you
in jail this time?

482
00:24:56,375 --> 00:24:59,294
Melanie: Jake and
his big, fat mouth.

483
00:24:59,336 --> 00:25:02,422
It's just a misunderstanding,
that's all.

484
00:25:02,464 --> 00:25:04,549
Yeah, kinda like that
weddin' I paid for, huh?

485
00:25:04,633 --> 00:25:06,885
I would hardly call that
a wedding.

486
00:25:06,969 --> 00:25:08,262
Boy was nervous.

487
00:25:08,303 --> 00:25:11,556
He was still drunk
from the night before.

488
00:25:11,640 --> 00:25:13,058
Can you blame him?

489
00:25:13,141 --> 00:25:14,977
Yes, I can!

490
00:25:15,060 --> 00:25:17,229
I went to the reception
by myself with puke

491
00:25:17,312 --> 00:25:20,315
all down my dress while he slept
it off in the Travelodge,

492
00:25:20,399 --> 00:25:22,276
and you're still
siding with that...

493
00:25:22,317 --> 00:25:24,361
I'm not sidin' with anybody.

494
00:25:24,444 --> 00:25:25,529
...[Sighs]
...[Sighs]

495
00:25:25,612 --> 00:25:26,780
The boy's changed, is all.

496
00:25:26,863 --> 00:25:29,032
Can we just
not talk about Jake, okay?

497
00:25:29,116 --> 00:25:31,785
l-I know he's the son you never
had, but I'm your only daughter,

498
00:25:31,868 --> 00:25:34,955
and maybe you want to know
what's new with me.

499
00:25:34,997 --> 00:25:38,166
[Sighs] Okay, shoot.

500
00:25:38,250 --> 00:25:41,878
I met somebody...

501
00:25:41,962 --> 00:25:45,257
and he's quite a catch.

502
00:25:45,340 --> 00:25:48,594
H-He's really a great guy.

503
00:25:48,677 --> 00:25:51,805
And I'm happy... really.

504
00:25:55,851 --> 00:25:57,811
Come to Mama, sugar!

505
00:25:59,771 --> 00:26:01,273
Hey, Mama.

506
00:26:01,356 --> 00:26:05,360
Oh, good land of the livin',
you are skin and bones.

507
00:26:07,195 --> 00:26:09,448
Well, don't I get a smile?

508
00:26:09,531 --> 00:26:11,617
I know you got one
in there somewhere.

509
00:26:11,700 --> 00:26:14,494
Come on, come on, let's not
let all the bought air out.

510
00:26:20,250 --> 00:26:22,836
Well, are you hungry, sweetie?

511
00:26:22,878 --> 00:26:25,213
Do you want me to reheat you
some chicken-fried steak?

512
00:26:25,297 --> 00:26:26,798
Oh, no, Mama, I'm fine.

513
00:26:26,882 --> 00:26:28,175
Sweetie, you look tired.

514
00:26:28,258 --> 00:26:30,218
Are you tired?
Oh, you know what?

515
00:26:30,260 --> 00:26:33,013
Maybe it's the way
you're wearing your hair now.

516
00:26:34,723 --> 00:26:35,891
[Sighs]

517
00:26:35,974 --> 00:26:37,768
You guys have really done
a lot with the place.

518
00:26:37,851 --> 00:26:39,853
Lord, would you listen
to that accent?

519
00:26:39,937 --> 00:26:41,897
Why don't you sit
in my good chair?

520
00:26:41,939 --> 00:26:44,232
Now, your mama got me this
Christmas before last.

521
00:26:44,316 --> 00:26:47,069
Oh, you mean the one where you
were supposed to come visit me?

522
00:26:47,152 --> 00:26:50,572
I told you time and time again,
it just didn't suit.

523
00:26:50,614 --> 00:26:53,075
Let me... let me get
you those tickets.

524
00:26:55,619 --> 00:26:58,330
Sit down in it.
Sit down.

525
00:26:58,413 --> 00:27:00,832
[Chair squeaks]

526
00:27:00,916 --> 00:27:02,709
Now, watch this.

527
00:27:02,793 --> 00:27:03,543
[Clicking]

528
00:27:03,585 --> 00:27:05,003
...Ahh!
...[Springs boing]

529
00:27:05,087 --> 00:27:06,546
...Oh! Oh!
...[Squeaking]

530
00:27:06,588 --> 00:27:08,757
I mean, isn't that
quite the deal?

531
00:27:08,840 --> 00:27:10,175
There are hardly words.

532
00:27:10,259 --> 00:27:12,427
Now, how do I get
out of this thing?

533
00:27:12,511 --> 00:27:14,721
...Oh...
...[Clicking]

534
00:27:14,763 --> 00:27:16,598
...Oh, my God!
...[Springs boing]

535
00:27:16,682 --> 00:27:19,434
Jake tell you
he's thinkin' of gettin' one?

536
00:27:19,518 --> 00:27:22,354
...[Sighs]
...Oh, I see your priorities...

537
00:27:22,437 --> 00:27:24,064
Jake, jail, and then home.

538
00:27:24,147 --> 00:27:27,109
Mama, it was just unfinished
business, is all.

539
00:27:27,150 --> 00:27:29,903
Jake's doin' all right.
Boy's goin' places.

540
00:27:29,987 --> 00:27:32,406
Once upon a time,
you were goin' places, too.

541
00:27:32,447 --> 00:27:35,200
Here are your tickets.

542
00:27:35,284 --> 00:27:36,368
These were a gift.

543
00:27:36,451 --> 00:27:38,412
I'd rather you guys
just use them.

544
00:27:43,500 --> 00:27:45,794
You know what I can't understand
is how y'all will visit

545
00:27:45,877 --> 00:27:48,088
every stupid battlefield
in the continental U.S.,

546
00:27:48,171 --> 00:27:50,966
but you can't manage
to visit your only daughter.

547
00:27:51,049 --> 00:27:53,010
Well, the door swings
both ways, sweetie.

548
00:27:53,093 --> 00:27:56,263
Anyway, don't get me started on
the things I don't understand.

549
00:27:56,305 --> 00:27:57,598
Here we go.

550
00:27:57,639 --> 00:28:00,183
Your dream for me was to get out
of this place and be somebody.

551
00:28:00,267 --> 00:28:02,728
You shoved me in every beauty
pageant in the state.

552
00:28:02,811 --> 00:28:04,271
I'm just sayin', is all.

553
00:28:04,313 --> 00:28:06,648
What?! What are you
trying to say?!

554
00:28:06,732 --> 00:28:09,067
l-I mean, just tell me what
I can do to make you happy!

555
00:28:09,151 --> 00:28:10,777
Just make yourself happy,
darlin'.

556
00:28:10,819 --> 00:28:13,447
Done.
We're there, all right?

557
00:28:13,488 --> 00:28:15,490
You know, I've really
made something of myself.

558
00:28:15,574 --> 00:28:18,285
I have a career. People
actually want to be me.

559
00:28:18,327 --> 00:28:21,455
And somebody loves me,
and I love him.

560
00:28:27,669 --> 00:28:31,048
Pearl, why don't you get us that
baloney cake out the icebox?

561
00:28:37,596 --> 00:28:40,682
Your mama's a complex woman.

562
00:28:40,766 --> 00:28:42,809
[Sighs] I'm going to bed.

563
00:28:46,188 --> 00:28:47,981
Good night, darlin'.

564
00:28:53,612 --> 00:28:55,113
Kate:
But you know nothing about her.

565
00:28:55,197 --> 00:28:57,324
Are you even sure who she is?

566
00:28:57,407 --> 00:28:58,784
I love her, Mom.

567
00:28:58,867 --> 00:29:00,077
That's nice,
but you have to be careful.

568
00:29:00,160 --> 00:29:02,037
You and I are different.

569
00:29:02,120 --> 00:29:04,831
We're not better, not worse...
we're just different.

570
00:29:04,873 --> 00:29:06,833
We're in public life to serve,
and to serve

571
00:29:06,875 --> 00:29:09,836
to the best of our abilities,
we have to set good examples.

572
00:29:09,878 --> 00:29:11,630
Do you have to control
everything?

573
00:29:11,713 --> 00:29:14,258
I've put a hold on the Plaza
for the second weekend in June.

574
00:29:14,341 --> 00:29:16,009
That should give you
a nice, long engagement.

575
00:29:16,051 --> 00:29:19,346
We were thinking
Christmas in Ireland.

576
00:29:19,429 --> 00:29:21,682
[Silverware clinks]

577
00:29:21,723 --> 00:29:23,642
If you think
I'm going to let some girl

578
00:29:23,725 --> 00:29:25,185
talk you into getting married

579
00:29:25,269 --> 00:29:27,145
...She is not "some girl."
...any place but New York City.

580
00:29:27,229 --> 00:29:29,815
She's my fiancee,
for Christ's sake.

581
00:29:29,898 --> 00:29:32,818
[Exhales sharply]

582
00:29:32,901 --> 00:29:35,070
You are just
like your father.

583
00:29:35,153 --> 00:29:39,866
One minute you're brilliant,
controlled, steadfast.

584
00:29:39,908 --> 00:29:42,035
The next you're
throwing it all away

585
00:29:42,077 --> 00:29:43,829
on some young piece of ass.

586
00:29:46,081 --> 00:29:48,417
Those are your issues, Mother.
[Clears throat]

587
00:29:48,500 --> 00:29:49,876
Not mine.

588
00:29:49,918 --> 00:29:53,714
[Birds chirping]

589
00:29:53,755 --> 00:29:56,091
[Dog barking]

590
00:29:57,009 --> 00:29:59,428
Melanie: Okay...

591
00:30:00,846 --> 00:30:03,140
Hold on.

592
00:30:03,223 --> 00:30:04,933
You know what? Uh...

593
00:30:05,017 --> 00:30:08,437
How long does
a contested divorce take?

594
00:30:08,520 --> 00:30:10,814
18 months?!

595
00:30:10,897 --> 00:30:13,942
Mr. Buford,
I don't have 18 months.

596
00:30:14,026 --> 00:30:16,653
I don't have 18 days.

597
00:30:16,737 --> 00:30:19,114
Okay, well, that's just
not gonna work for me.

598
00:30:19,197 --> 00:30:21,116
...U- Uh, ye-yes.
...Man: Whoo-hoo!

599
00:30:21,158 --> 00:30:24,077
Don't see the likes of you
around these here parts much!

600
00:30:24,119 --> 00:30:25,954
Mr. Buford,
that's not gonna work.

601
00:30:26,038 --> 00:30:29,249
Lady, you look like
sex on a stick in that

602
00:30:29,291 --> 00:30:31,084
...Frederick Montana getup!
...I have to call you back.

603
00:30:31,168 --> 00:30:32,920
Listen, bubba,
why don't you just kiss my...

604
00:30:34,463 --> 00:30:37,257
...ass!
Oh, my God!

605
00:30:37,341 --> 00:30:38,926
Get in the truck, there, missy,

606
00:30:39,009 --> 00:30:41,428
'cause I don't do that sort
of thing on the street.

607
00:30:42,512 --> 00:30:44,973
I guess your mama
raised you right.

608
00:30:45,015 --> 00:30:48,435
Whoo! What is that? [Sniffs]
Calvin Klein? That's very nice.

609
00:30:48,477 --> 00:30:50,771
Very good.
l-I better back off.

610
00:30:50,854 --> 00:30:53,690
Don't want to get you in trouble
with the little lady.

611
00:30:53,774 --> 00:30:56,234
There is a little lady,
isn't there?

612
00:30:56,318 --> 00:31:00,155
I can hardly afford me, much
less some high-maintenance babe.

613
00:31:00,238 --> 00:31:01,448
What about
Cindy What's-her-name?

614
00:31:01,531 --> 00:31:03,784
You guys were real hot
and heavy in high school.

615
00:31:03,825 --> 00:31:06,787
She's a women's softball coach
up in Nashville.

616
00:31:06,828 --> 00:31:09,706
...Mm-hmm. [Chuckles]
...Oh...

617
00:31:09,790 --> 00:31:12,376
Well, that explains some
lingering questions that I had

618
00:31:12,459 --> 00:31:14,586
about a game of post office
we played one time.

619
00:31:14,670 --> 00:31:16,922
...[Laughing] No!
...[Laughs]

620
00:31:17,005 --> 00:31:20,300
I guess we all have our little
secrets, don't we, Bobby Ray?

621
00:31:22,219 --> 00:31:24,179
Yeah, we sure do.

622
00:31:25,889 --> 00:31:28,684
'Course, I read about
yours on the Internet.

623
00:31:28,767 --> 00:31:30,143
What?!

624
00:31:30,227 --> 00:31:32,479
Oh, I know all about
the cocks in your henhouse.

625
00:31:32,562 --> 00:31:34,815
Oh, God!
Bobby Ray!

626
00:31:34,898 --> 00:31:36,483
You sure do know how
to make a girl blush.

627
00:31:36,525 --> 00:31:38,527
Well, I gotta get back
to the factory,

628
00:31:38,568 --> 00:31:39,945
but are you in town
for a while?

629
00:31:40,028 --> 00:31:41,947
Oh, God, I hope not. No,
I'm just hitting the bank.

630
00:31:42,030 --> 00:31:44,658
Well, I better scram.

631
00:31:44,700 --> 00:31:45,993
Ha ha. Very funny.

632
00:31:46,034 --> 00:31:48,328
...Been really good to see you.
...Good to see you, too.

633
00:31:48,370 --> 00:31:49,496
[Smooches]
Bye.

634
00:31:49,579 --> 00:31:52,040
[Door opens]

635
00:31:52,082 --> 00:31:55,168
Oh... hi, Eugene.

636
00:31:55,252 --> 00:31:57,337
How's your leg?

637
00:31:57,421 --> 00:32:00,048
Oh, it don't give me too much
trouble, Miss Melanie.

638
00:32:00,132 --> 00:32:03,093
Dorothea, I'm gonna
take my lunch.

639
00:32:03,176 --> 00:32:05,637
[Telephone rings]

640
00:32:08,223 --> 00:32:10,517
Well, look what
the cat dragged in.

641
00:32:12,978 --> 00:32:14,229
Dorothea?!

642
00:32:14,313 --> 00:32:16,523
Oh, my God, you've...

643
00:32:16,565 --> 00:32:18,650
Lost 110 pounds,
I know.

644
00:32:18,734 --> 00:32:23,405
[Exhales sharply]
Well... congratulations.

645
00:32:23,488 --> 00:32:24,698
Thanks.

646
00:32:24,781 --> 00:32:27,367
Uh... I noticed that you
don't have an ATM.

647
00:32:27,451 --> 00:32:29,453
Oh, them things.
Russ don't want to put one in

648
00:32:29,536 --> 00:32:33,332
on account of you lose personal
contact with the customers.

649
00:32:33,415 --> 00:32:35,751
Yes, that would be tragic.

650
00:32:37,878 --> 00:32:41,214
Wade said you and Jake
had quite the reunion.

651
00:32:41,256 --> 00:32:43,508
But that's just
pillow talk talkin'.

652
00:32:43,592 --> 00:32:46,511
A-Are you and Wade...

653
00:32:46,595 --> 00:32:48,722
Goin' on three years.

654
00:32:48,805 --> 00:32:50,432
'Course,
it ain't Tiffany's.

655
00:32:50,515 --> 00:32:52,059
But then again,

656
00:32:52,100 --> 00:32:54,102
you can't believe
everything you hear on TV.

657
00:32:54,144 --> 00:32:56,605
Uh, l-I need to make
a withdraw from my...

658
00:32:56,688 --> 00:32:57,898
Joint account?

659
00:32:57,981 --> 00:32:58,732
My what?

660
00:33:01,610 --> 00:33:02,778
with Jake.

661
00:33:02,861 --> 00:33:06,281
From what I hear,
y'all are still married.

662
00:33:08,659 --> 00:33:10,160
Why, yes.

663
00:33:12,162 --> 00:33:14,122
Yes, we are.

664
00:33:14,164 --> 00:33:16,917
# I got a little change
in my pocket #

665
00:33:16,959 --> 00:33:18,961
# Goin' jing-a-ling-a-ling #

666
00:33:19,044 --> 00:33:21,546
# Want to call you on
the telephone, baby #

667
00:33:21,630 --> 00:33:23,924
# And give you a ring #

668
00:33:24,007 --> 00:33:25,384
# But each time we talk #

669
00:33:25,467 --> 00:33:27,219
# I get the same old thing #

670
00:33:27,302 --> 00:33:29,429
# Always
"No huggy, no kissy #

671
00:33:29,471 --> 00:33:31,515
# Until I get a wedding ring" #

672
00:33:31,598 --> 00:33:33,517
# Oh, my honey, my baby #

673
00:33:33,600 --> 00:33:35,602
# Don't put my love
