674
00:33:35,686 --> 00:33:37,771
# She said,
"Don't hand me no lines #

675
00:33:37,854 --> 00:33:39,731
# And keep
your hands to yourself" #

676
00:33:48,365 --> 00:33:50,450
# B-Baby, baby, baby #

677
00:33:50,534 --> 00:33:52,327
# Why you treat me this way? #

678
00:33:52,411 --> 00:33:54,288
# You know I'm still
your lover boy... #

679
00:33:54,371 --> 00:33:56,832
[Groans]

680
00:33:56,915 --> 00:33:59,751
Hi, honey.

681
00:33:59,835 --> 00:34:03,463
Lookin' good.
How's the family?

682
00:34:04,923 --> 00:34:08,343
Cut the shit.
Where's my stuff?

683
00:34:08,427 --> 00:34:09,803
Now, what kind of wife
would I be

684
00:34:09,886 --> 00:34:12,014
if I didn't pick up
after my husband?

685
00:34:13,098 --> 00:34:15,976
The kind that
don't live here.

686
00:34:16,018 --> 00:34:18,145
Now, I'm gonna ask you
one last time.

687
00:34:18,228 --> 00:34:20,689
Where is the Hide-A-Key?!

688
00:34:20,772 --> 00:34:24,985
I had the sweetest chat with
Wade's mama about her tractor.

689
00:34:26,945 --> 00:34:29,156
Nice to see you got
your accent back.

690
00:34:29,239 --> 00:34:32,701
Oh, I stumbled across
a few things today.

691
00:34:32,743 --> 00:34:33,869
Holy shit!

692
00:34:33,952 --> 00:34:36,038
What happened to the stove?!

693
00:34:36,121 --> 00:34:38,957
Oh, and where are
them little magnets

694
00:34:39,041 --> 00:34:41,460
I had over here, huh?!

695
00:34:45,255 --> 00:34:47,966
What the hell is this...
chick food?

696
00:34:48,050 --> 00:34:51,678
Light beer... less calories.

697
00:34:51,720 --> 00:34:53,263
I tried to pick out
a new bed,

698
00:34:53,347 --> 00:34:55,724
but have you been to
the Sit 'n Sleep lately?

699
00:34:55,807 --> 00:34:59,019
Yuck. I'll just have to order
something from New York.

700
00:34:59,102 --> 00:35:01,480
Whatever blows
your dress up, darlin'.

701
00:35:01,563 --> 00:35:04,024
You go right ahead
and spend your money.

702
00:35:04,107 --> 00:35:05,651
Oh, but, darlin'...

703
00:35:05,734 --> 00:35:07,861
I thought you said we should
think of it as...

704
00:35:07,945 --> 00:35:09,321
our money.

705
00:35:14,076 --> 00:35:15,327
Just a guess,

706
00:35:15,410 --> 00:35:17,746
but I'm thinking the words
"joint checking"

707
00:35:17,829 --> 00:35:19,957
are flashing in your head
right now.

708
00:35:27,965 --> 00:35:29,383
How much did you take?

709
00:35:29,466 --> 00:35:31,218
All of it.

710
00:35:31,301 --> 00:35:32,719
Son of a bitch!

711
00:35:32,761 --> 00:35:35,681
You want a wife,
you got a wife.

712
00:35:35,764 --> 00:35:37,849
And what are you doing
with all that cash?

713
00:35:37,933 --> 00:35:39,893
Why don't you invest it?
Don't you know anything?!

714
00:35:39,977 --> 00:35:41,728
I know if you don't get out
of this house right now...

715
00:35:41,770 --> 00:35:44,231
Sign the papers, and
I'll give it all back.

716
00:35:44,273 --> 00:35:45,232
...Fine!
...Fine!

717
00:35:45,274 --> 00:35:46,817
Give me the pen.

718
00:35:46,900 --> 00:35:50,904
Hold on. What are you doing
with all that cash saved up?

719
00:35:50,988 --> 00:35:52,739
And since when did you
quit the tire factory?

720
00:35:52,823 --> 00:35:54,783
You're not doing anything
illegal, are you, Jake?!

721
00:35:54,866 --> 00:35:57,077
Maybe I am. So what?

722
00:35:57,160 --> 00:35:58,662
I don't ask you about
your boyfriend,

723
00:35:58,745 --> 00:36:01,415
you keep your nose
out of my life... deal?

724
00:36:05,460 --> 00:36:06,920
Who told you?

725
00:36:06,962 --> 00:36:11,091
Honey, just 'cause I talk slow
doesn't mean I'm stupid.

726
00:36:18,724 --> 00:36:20,559
Look, Jake...

727
00:36:20,642 --> 00:36:24,605
Nobody finds their soul mate
when they're 10 years old.

728
00:36:27,024 --> 00:36:30,485
Yeah, I guess.

729
00:36:30,527 --> 00:36:33,030
I mean, where's
the fun in that, right?

730
00:36:47,336 --> 00:36:49,963
I can't believe you kept
this thing all these years.

731
00:36:50,047 --> 00:36:52,633
Mm-hmm.

732
00:36:52,716 --> 00:36:55,844
Most people don't know that
lightning does that to sand.

733
00:36:55,928 --> 00:36:59,640
Oh, hey, Mel,
you know what?

734
00:36:59,723 --> 00:37:00,849
[Chuckles]

735
00:37:00,933 --> 00:37:03,060
I just remembered
I got myself a hot date.

736
00:37:03,143 --> 00:37:05,729
You don't mind if I have
my lawyer take a look at these.

737
00:37:05,812 --> 00:37:06,855
What?!

738
00:37:06,939 --> 00:37:10,692
Hell, I'm just a
simple country boy.

739
00:37:10,776 --> 00:37:13,862
There's words in there
I can't even pronounce.

740
00:37:13,946 --> 00:37:16,531
You might be takin' me to
the cleaners for all I know.

741
00:37:16,615 --> 00:37:18,325
The cleaners? You?

742
00:37:18,408 --> 00:37:20,953
Say, what did this set
you back, anyhow?

743
00:37:21,036 --> 00:37:22,371
More than you
make in a month.

