00:49:37,648 --> 00:49:39,483
How deep is that water?

995
00:49:39,566 --> 00:49:40,651
About 8 feet.

996
00:49:40,734 --> 00:49:42,152
[Bryant groans]

997
00:49:45,697 --> 00:49:49,743
Look, Mel...
I signed your papers.

998
00:49:52,454 --> 00:49:54,498
Jake, I never
meant to hurt you,

999
00:49:54,581 --> 00:49:56,583
or anybody else,
for that matter.

1000
00:49:56,667 --> 00:50:00,170
And I just came out
here to say...

1001
00:50:00,254 --> 00:50:01,922
thank you.

1002
00:50:04,508 --> 00:50:07,552
You might want to find yourself
a place out of the way.

1003
00:50:09,638 --> 00:50:10,931
You can't just leave!

1004
00:50:11,014 --> 00:50:12,599
[Chuckles]

1005
00:50:12,683 --> 00:50:14,935
Sure I can.

1006
00:50:15,018 --> 00:50:16,520
You want to come?

1007
00:50:18,355 --> 00:50:19,439
Where you goin'?

1008
00:50:19,523 --> 00:50:21,608
Well...

1009
00:50:24,611 --> 00:50:26,446
I want to show you
somethin'.

1010
00:50:29,491 --> 00:50:30,951
I can't.

1011
00:50:32,911 --> 00:50:34,329
Can't or won't?

1012
00:50:35,747 --> 00:50:37,040
Both.

1013
00:50:37,124 --> 00:50:39,793
The girl I knew
used to be fearless.

1014
00:50:39,876 --> 00:50:41,628
The girl you knew
didn't have a life.

1015
00:50:41,712 --> 00:50:46,550
Well, I... guess you better
get on with it, then.

1016
00:50:46,633 --> 00:50:47,968
Come on, Bryant!

1017
00:50:50,012 --> 00:50:53,140
Come on, boy,
get in here.

1018
00:51:07,029 --> 00:51:09,656
E-Excuse me, do you know
Bobby Ray Bailey's address?

1019
00:51:09,698 --> 00:51:12,492
8 13 Lafayette.

1020
00:51:15,037 --> 00:51:16,872
You don't remember me,
do you?

1021
00:51:16,955 --> 00:51:19,416
Oh, I remember you
just fine.

1022
00:51:19,499 --> 00:51:22,669
You used to steal
catfish from my pond.

1023
00:51:24,463 --> 00:51:26,465
Yes, sir.

1024
00:51:26,548 --> 00:51:28,800
I did that.

1025
00:51:28,884 --> 00:51:30,510
I'm sorry.

1026
00:51:32,554 --> 00:51:33,931
'Course, on the weekends,

1027
00:51:34,014 --> 00:51:36,975
Bobby Ray goes over to
the Carmichael plantation...

1028
00:51:37,059 --> 00:51:38,644
visits with Colonel Murphy...

1029
00:51:38,727 --> 00:51:40,646
it being tourist
season and all.

1030
00:51:40,729 --> 00:51:41,897
Thank you.

1031
00:51:43,565 --> 00:51:45,817
[Birds chirping,
dog barking]

1032
00:51:54,493 --> 00:51:55,369
Yes?

1033
00:51:55,452 --> 00:51:58,372
Oh, hi! [Chuckles]
I'm Melanie Carmi...

1034
00:51:58,455 --> 00:52:02,626
um, um, Melanie Smooter.

1035
00:52:02,709 --> 00:52:04,544
I'm... I'm here
to see Bobby Ray.

1036
00:52:04,628 --> 00:52:05,629
[Cannon fires]

1037
00:52:05,712 --> 00:52:06,922
...Oh.
...Yee-haw!

1038
00:52:07,005 --> 00:52:09,383
If he's alive,
he's out back.

1039
00:52:09,424 --> 00:52:11,218
Come on.

1040
00:52:12,636 --> 00:52:15,555
They're out here somewhere.
Watch your step.

1041
00:52:22,437 --> 00:52:23,563
Bobby Ray?

1042
00:52:23,647 --> 00:52:25,649
Bobby Ray: Melanie?!

1043
00:52:25,732 --> 00:52:27,234
Don't move!

1044
00:52:27,317 --> 00:52:29,569
Yee-haw!

1045
00:52:29,611 --> 00:52:31,405
[Cannonball whirring]

1046
00:52:35,075 --> 00:52:36,910
Hot damn!

1047
00:52:36,952 --> 00:52:39,579
Hold your fire, sir.
I'll be right back.

1048
00:52:43,959 --> 00:52:45,752
We weren't aimin' for ya,

1049
00:52:45,794 --> 00:52:48,213
but I doubt I would have
gone to your funeral.

1050
00:52:50,966 --> 00:52:54,303
I guess I wouldn't blame you.

1051
00:52:58,348 --> 00:53:01,518
Forgotten how beautiful
this place was.

1052
00:53:01,602 --> 00:53:04,813
Guess it doesn't take much
to forget a lot of things.

1053
00:53:04,896 --> 00:53:07,190
Bobby Ray,
it's not like that.

1054
00:53:07,274 --> 00:53:09,735
You know what? I'll tell
you what it's not like.

1055
00:53:09,818 --> 00:53:13,447
It's not like Jake's the only
one that you run out on.

1056
00:53:15,949 --> 00:53:18,118
I'm so sorry I outed you.

1057
00:53:19,995 --> 00:53:22,664
I guess I figured
if I was pointing at you,

1058
00:53:22,748 --> 00:53:26,835
then... nobody would
see through me.

1059
00:53:26,919 --> 00:53:31,214
Bobby Ray,
I can't find the fuse!

1060
00:53:36,845 --> 00:53:39,473
I should go
before he kills himself.

1061
00:53:47,105 --> 00:53:49,232
Bye.

1062
00:54:01,036 --> 00:54:02,663
Afternoon.

1063
00:54:02,704 --> 00:54:04,331
Can I help you?

1064
00:54:04,373 --> 00:54:06,375
Barry Lowenstein,
"New York Post."

1065
00:54:06,458 --> 00:54:10,379
Ho-ho, boy,
am I glad to see you.

1066
00:54:10,462 --> 00:54:11,838
I'll tell you, it's, uh...

1067
00:54:11,880 --> 00:54:16,009
definitely, uh,
another world down here.

1068
00:54:16,093 --> 00:54:17,678
Uh, did you say
the "Post"?

1069
00:54:17,761 --> 00:54:19,221
Yes, I did.
l-I was hoping

1070
00:54:19,304 --> 00:54:21,139
to get an interview
with you and your family...

1071
00:54:21,223 --> 00:54:24,017
maybe, um, a few pictures
if you don't mind?

1072
00:54:24,059 --> 00:54:26,937
No.
I mean, uh, yes, I do...

1073
00:54:27,020 --> 00:54:27,938
mind.

1074
00:54:28,021 --> 00:54:29,231
They're not here.

1075
00:54:29,314 --> 00:54:31,483
Oh... wow.

1076
00:54:31,566 --> 00:54:33,568
This is just
as you described it.

1077
00:54:33,652 --> 00:54:37,447
It must have been amazing,
huh, growing up here?

1078
00:54:37,531 --> 00:54:39,199
Like a fantasy.

1079
00:54:39,283 --> 00:54:42,953
Would you mind if I take
a quick look inside?

1080
00:54:43,036 --> 00:54:44,454
Actually,
I'm on my way out.

1081
00:54:44,538 --> 00:54:46,373
I'll come back, then.

1082
00:54:46,415 --> 00:54:48,292
Uh, uh, okay,
but just a peek.

1083
00:54:48,375 --> 00:54:49,376
[Chuckles]

1084
00:54:51,878 --> 00:54:54,214
This is it...
home sweet home.

1085
00:54:54,298 --> 00:54:55,549
Wow!

1086
00:54:55,591 --> 00:54:57,259
How old is this place?

1087
00:54:57,342 --> 00:54:58,635
Uh...

1088
00:54:58,719 --> 00:55:02,931
it was built by my, uh,
great-great-great-grandfather,

1089
00:55:03,015 --> 00:55:04,558
Charles Carmichael,
in 1853.

1090
00:55:04,641 --> 00:55:08,478
Oh, boy, I bet you slid down
this banister a time or two.

1091
00:55:08,562 --> 00:55:09,521
Oh.

1092
00:55:09,605 --> 00:55:13,775
And over here we have
the, um...

1093
00:55:13,859 --> 00:55:16,236
[Maid humming]

1094
00:55:16,278 --> 00:55:18,739
...kitchen, but who hasn't
seen one of those?

1095
00:55:18,780 --> 00:55:19,906
Let's start over here.

1096
00:55:22,618 --> 00:55:24,453
[Door knob rattles]

1097
00:55:25,329 --> 00:55:26,663
[Humming continues]

1098
00:55:26,747 --> 00:55:28,248
[Gasps] Oh.

1099
00:55:29,666 --> 00:55:31,960
[Humming continues]

1100
00:55:34,796 --> 00:55:36,632
[Whispering] Now, this is
my favorite room.

1101
00:55:36,715 --> 00:55:41,678
It was part of the, um,
Underground Railroad.

1102
00:55:41,762 --> 00:55:44,181
[Whispering]
Why are we whispering?

1103
00:55:44,264 --> 00:55:47,059
The whole place
is haunted...

1104
00:55:47,142 --> 00:55:52,397
by ghosts of, um,
the Civil War soldiers.

1105
00:55:54,733 --> 00:55:57,152
[Door hinges creak]

1106
00:55:59,529 --> 00:56:01,949
[Creaking]

1107
00:56:03,951 --> 00:56:08,038
Jake! [Muttering]
...buttons.

1108
00:56:08,121 --> 00:56:10,666
No wonder we lost the war.

1109
00:56:12,501 --> 00:56:15,045
Was that one of 'em?

1110
00:56:15,128 --> 00:56:17,965
Melanie?

1111
00:56:18,006 --> 00:56:20,634
What are you doin'
in a closet?

1112
00:56:20,676 --> 00:56:23,178
Hi. Barry Lowenstein,
"New York Post."

1113
00:56:23,220 --> 00:56:26,473
Miss Carmichael is just showing
me around the plantation.

1114
00:56:28,684 --> 00:56:31,979
Uh, Mr. Lowenstein is writing
a piece on the family,

1115
00:56:32,020 --> 00:56:35,274
you know, since I'm marrying
the mayor's son and all.

1116
00:56:35,357 --> 00:56:37,985
I had no idea.
Isn't that something?

1117
00:56:39,528 --> 00:56:40,862
Yeah.

1118
00:56:43,240 --> 00:56:46,201
Well, a plantation by any
other name is just a farm.

1119
00:56:46,285 --> 00:56:48,620
But it does roll off the tongue
a little sweeter, doesn't it?

1120
00:56:48,704 --> 00:56:49,830
Huh.

1121
00:56:49,913 --> 00:56:53,917
Well, I do believe Miss Melanie
forgot her manners.

1122
00:56:54,001 --> 00:56:56,837
I'm Bobby Ray...
her cousin.

1123
00:56:56,878 --> 00:56:58,880
[Sighs]

1124
00:56:58,964 --> 00:57:00,340
Charmed.

1125
00:57:03,510 --> 00:57:05,887
See, when the Yankees
marched through Alabama,

1126
00:57:05,971 --> 00:57:08,640
they tried to destroy
our metal-formin' capabilities

1127
00:57:08,724 --> 00:57:11,351
by placin' barrels of powder
underneath the anvils.

1128
00:57:11,393 --> 00:57:13,186
Of course,
all that managed to do

1129
00:57:13,270 --> 00:57:15,397
was blow 'em sky-high
for a few seconds.

1130
00:57:15,480 --> 00:57:18,066
So... in honor
of that act of stupidity,

1131
00:57:18,150 --> 00:57:22,029
we all... we get together to
re-create it for the tourists.

1132
00:57:29,870 --> 00:57:31,580
...[Cannon fires]
...Aah!

1133
00:57:31,663 --> 00:57:34,166
...Yee-haw!
...What the hell was that?!

1134
00:57:34,249 --> 00:57:35,208
[Cannonball whirring]

1135
00:57:35,250 --> 00:57:38,128
Hey, Grandpa!
This here's Barry!

1136
00:57:38,211 --> 00:57:40,797
He's doin' an article
on Melanie's weddin'!

1137
00:57:40,881 --> 00:57:43,884
Never heard of her.

1138
00:57:52,309 --> 00:57:54,102
Thanks!

1139
00:57:54,186 --> 00:57:57,439
[Tires screeching]

1140
00:57:57,522 --> 00:58:01,735
Well, aren't you
just a big, fat liar.

1141
00:58:01,818 --> 00:58:03,779
Bobby Ray!

1142
00:58:03,862 --> 00:58:05,238
Oh, go back to New York.

1143
00:58:05,322 --> 00:58:06,573
[Both laugh]

1144
00:58:10,786 --> 00:58:14,706
# If fear's
what makes us decide #

1145
00:58:14,790 --> 00:58:18,919
# Our future journey #

1146
00:58:18,961 --> 00:58:21,755
# Well, I'm not along
for a life #

1147
00:58:21,797 --> 00:58:23,465
# I'm not along for a life #

1148
00:58:23,548 --> 00:58:25,717
# 'Cause I'm still yearning #

1149
00:58:25,801 --> 00:58:31,682
# l-l-I am falling down #

1150
00:58:31,765 --> 00:58:34,017
# Try and stop me #

1151
00:58:34,101 --> 00:58:39,773
# It feels so good
to hit the ground #

1152
00:58:39,856 --> 00:58:42,150
# You can watch me #

1153
00:58:42,234 --> 00:58:45,112
# I fall right on my face #

1154
00:58:45,195 --> 00:58:49,908
# It's an uphill human race #

1155
00:58:49,992 --> 00:58:55,330
# And l-I am falling down #

1156
00:58:55,414 --> 00:58:58,333
Hmm. Hello.

1157
00:58:58,417 --> 00:59:00,836
I'm sorry about what I said.

1158
00:59:00,919 --> 00:59:02,212
Really sorry.

1159
00:59:02,296 --> 00:59:04,464
Melanie, forget it.

1160
00:59:04,548 --> 00:59:06,842
Boy:
She was not sharing.

1161
00:59:06,925 --> 00:59:10,137
Okay, y'all, you need
to eat and be quiet.

1162
00:59:10,220 --> 00:59:12,014
We're gonna have us
a little visit.

1163
00:59:12,097 --> 00:59:13,849
# Ye-a, ye-a, ye-a, yeah #

1164
00:59:13,932 --> 00:59:20,647
# Oh, l-l-I am falling down #

1165
00:59:20,689 --> 00:59:23,108
# Try and stop me #

1166
00:59:23,191 --> 00:59:26,153
# It feels so good
to hit the ground #

1167
00:59:26,194 --> 00:59:29,531
You know, he went up there.

1168
00:59:29,615 --> 00:59:31,992
Who?

1169
00:59:32,075 --> 00:59:34,828
Jake? When?

1170
00:59:34,870 --> 00:59:38,081
About a year after you left.

1171
00:59:38,165 --> 00:59:41,835
He doesn't know I know,
but Clinton let it slip once.

1172
00:59:41,919 --> 00:59:43,420
Jake was in New York?

1173
00:59:43,503 --> 00:59:45,380
He told Clinton he'd never
seen anything like it.

1174
00:59:45,464 --> 00:59:47,174
He realized straight off

1175
00:59:47,215 --> 00:59:51,178
he'd need more than
an apology to win you back.

1176
00:59:51,261 --> 00:59:55,015
He needed to conquer
the world first.

1177
00:59:55,098 --> 00:59:56,892
He's been tryin' ever since.

1178
00:59:56,975 --> 01:00:00,187
That's why he kept
sending the papers back.

1179
01:00:00,228 --> 01:00:02,481
Yeah.

1180
01:00:02,564 --> 01:00:07,194
Hmm. It's funny
how things don't work out.

1181
01:00:07,277 --> 01:00:08,195
[Baby gurgles]

1182
01:00:08,278 --> 01:00:11,031
It's funny how they do.

1183
01:00:18,372 --> 01:00:20,332
[Cheers and applause]

1184
01:00:28,257 --> 01:00:29,758
# Now, listen here #

1185
01:00:29,841 --> 01:00:33,053
# Well, I tried to tell you,
baby #

1186
01:00:33,095 --> 01:00:35,514
# But that don't make
no sense #

1187
01:00:35,597 --> 01:00:38,976
# Now you got me, baby #

1188
01:00:39,059 --> 01:00:40,894
# Up against that fence #

1189
01:00:40,978 --> 01:00:45,565
...# Ain't that a shame? #
...# Shame #

1190
01:00:45,649 --> 01:00:47,776
# Shame, shame
the way you do #

1191
01:00:47,859 --> 01:00:50,570
Man: Ha-ha! Ha!

1192
01:00:53,156 --> 01:00:56,285
Hey, look who I found
hangin' out by the parkin' lot.

1193
01:00:56,368 --> 01:00:57,786
Hesitant to join us.

1194
01:00:57,869 --> 01:00:59,997
# Shame, shame,
shame on you #

1195
01:01:00,080 --> 01:01:02,040
Jake: Anybody think
of anything in here

1196
01:01:02,124 --> 01:01:04,418
that, uh, might bother
Bobby Ray?

1197
01:01:04,459 --> 01:01:07,129
...Uh, Clinton's breath?
...Ha!

1198
01:01:08,922 --> 01:01:10,882
You still the same Bobby Ray
from last night?

1199
01:01:10,966 --> 01:01:13,093
Last time I checked,
yeah.

1200
01:01:13,176 --> 01:01:16,513
Well, then, I'm gonna
buy you a drink.

1201
01:01:16,597 --> 01:01:19,141
Well, you're really not
my type, I mean...

1202
01:01:19,224 --> 01:01:22,728
[Laughter]

1203
01:01:26,523 --> 01:01:29,192
Oh, honey, you...
you drink that from the top.

1204
01:01:29,276 --> 01:01:32,738
I'm just lookin' to see who
makes this Deep South Glass.

1205
01:01:32,821 --> 01:01:34,781
I wonder if you can get it
in New York.

1206
01:01:34,823 --> 01:01:36,033
It's beautiful.

1207
01:01:36,116 --> 01:01:38,660
Hey, Jake,
Mel would like to know

1208
01:01:38,744 --> 01:01:42,623
where she can find some of
that snooty-faluty glass.

1209
01:01:42,664 --> 01:01:44,166
Why ask me?

1210
01:01:44,207 --> 01:01:46,168
Oh, I don't know.
Maybe because you're...

1211
01:01:46,251 --> 01:01:47,461
[Clears throat]

1212
01:01:47,502 --> 01:01:50,631
You're all spiffed up
and... and all.

1213
01:01:50,672 --> 01:01:53,342
...["Sweet Home Alabama" plays]
...Am I missin' somethin'?

1214
01:01:53,425 --> 01:01:57,471
...[Cheering]
...Let's show some respect.

1215
01:02:05,687 --> 01:02:07,648
Jake...

1216
01:02:07,689 --> 01:02:10,192
When was the last time you
pushed me around the floor?

1217
01:02:10,233 --> 01:02:12,277
Clinton here has got
two left feet.

1218
01:02:12,361 --> 01:02:14,696
Well, Ms. Taylor,
I'd be honored.

1219
01:02:14,780 --> 01:02:16,406
Let's do it. Come on.

1220
01:02:16,490 --> 01:02:18,450
Come on, Mel,
get on out here!

1221
01:02:18,533 --> 01:02:22,496
Well, aren't you
the Lord of the Dance?

1222
01:02:22,579 --> 01:02:26,083
I ain't as clumsy as I look.
She just can't keep time.

1223
01:02:26,166 --> 01:02:28,377
You might have to
prove that to me.

1224
01:02:36,718 --> 01:02:38,512
Woman: Whoo!

1225
01:02:38,595 --> 01:02:41,431
# Now, I heard Mr. Young
sing about her #

1226
01:02:43,642 --> 01:02:46,353
You know, he's pretty good.
It might be you.

1227
01:02:46,436 --> 01:02:48,855
Oh, the hell you say.
Let me at him.

1228
01:02:48,897 --> 01:02:52,859
# I hope Neil Young
will remember #

1229
01:02:52,943 --> 01:02:55,404
Aw, look at them two
welded together.

1230
01:02:55,487 --> 01:02:58,740
Why do they fight it?

1231
01:02:58,824 --> 01:03:00,784
# Sweet home Alabama #

1232
01:03:00,867 --> 01:03:04,955
Maybe we could just talk.

1233
01:03:07,833 --> 01:03:10,794
# Sweet home Alabama #

1234
01:03:13,130 --> 01:03:15,632
# Lord, I'm comin' home
to you #

1235
01:03:18,635 --> 01:03:22,055
[Crickets chirping,
dog barking]

1236
01:03:22,097 --> 01:03:24,808
[Train whistle blows]

1237
01:03:24,891 --> 01:03:27,352
Come on, let's go
to the Roadhouse.

1238
01:03:27,436 --> 01:03:28,979
Nah.

1239
01:03:29,062 --> 01:03:33,275
What do you say we drive
out to Fairview and bowl?

1240
01:03:33,358 --> 01:03:34,735
I don't think so.

1241
01:03:34,776 --> 01:03:36,695
Do you want to go
harass somebody?

1242
01:03:36,778 --> 01:03:39,740
...[Chuckles]
...Unh-unh.

1243
01:03:39,781 --> 01:03:42,075
Hey, I know this great
place where we can...

1244
01:03:42,159 --> 01:03:43,160
All: No!

1245
01:03:49,541 --> 01:03:53,337
Y'all, I think I'm gonna
call it a night.

1246
01:03:56,340 --> 01:03:57,716
[Thud]

1247
01:03:57,799 --> 01:03:59,760
[Sighs]

1248
01:04:01,261 --> 01:04:05,599
[Crickets chirping]

1249
01:04:05,682 --> 01:04:08,477
[Indistinct shouting
in distance]

1250
01:04:32,292 --> 01:04:34,836
Hi, there, boy.

1251
01:04:34,920 --> 01:04:37,798
Sorry it took me so long.

1252
01:04:37,881 --> 01:04:41,927
I would have come sooner
if I'd known you were sick.

1253
01:04:45,514 --> 01:04:49,810
Actually, that's
probably not true.

1254
01:04:49,893 --> 01:04:54,064
[Exhales sharply]
I've been pretty selfish lately.

1255
01:04:56,483 --> 01:04:59,653
Dogs don't know anything
about that, do they, though?

1256
01:05:02,572 --> 01:05:05,867
You were always
like a big old pillow.

1257
01:05:09,830 --> 01:05:15,377
Like when everything
went pear-shaped...

1258
01:05:15,460 --> 01:05:18,839
[Voice breaking]
you never left my side.

1259
01:05:24,595 --> 01:05:27,347
And then I just left you.

1260
01:05:34,563 --> 01:05:38,692
[Crying] I bet you sat there
wondering what you'd done wrong.

1261
01:05:43,530 --> 01:05:46,450
I told him
it was my fault.

1262
01:05:48,368 --> 01:05:50,537
[Sighs]

1263
01:05:50,621 --> 01:05:52,789
[Sniffs]
Quit bein' so nice.

1264
01:05:52,873 --> 01:05:55,292
It's the truth.

1265
01:05:55,375 --> 01:05:58,253
How come it has to be
so complicated?

1266
01:05:58,337 --> 01:05:59,338
What?

1267
01:05:59,421 --> 01:06:00,881
Truth...

1268
01:06:00,964 --> 01:06:05,218
[Sniffs] life...

1269
01:06:05,302 --> 01:06:07,262
this.

1270
01:06:09,640 --> 01:06:11,725
He was one hell
of a good dog, wasn't he?

1271
01:06:11,808 --> 01:06:15,062
[Sighs, sniffs]
Yeah.

1272
01:06:15,145 --> 01:06:19,691
You looked like you were
having fun out there tonight.

1273
01:06:21,944 --> 01:06:24,947
I'm happy
in New York, Jake.

1274
01:06:24,988 --> 01:06:27,407
[Sighs]

1275
01:06:27,449 --> 01:06:31,495
But then I come down here
and...

1276
01:06:31,578 --> 01:06:33,497
this fits, too.

1277
01:06:33,580 --> 01:06:36,750
Since when does it have to be
one or the other?

1278
01:06:36,792 --> 01:06:39,419
You can have roots
and wings, Mel.

1279
01:06:42,214 --> 01:06:44,591
Maybe I could just fly south
for the winter.

1280
01:06:48,595 --> 01:06:50,430
Look.

1281
01:06:50,472 --> 01:06:52,266
What?

1282
01:06:52,349 --> 01:06:54,309
There.
Do you see 'em?

1283
01:06:58,313 --> 01:07:00,607
[Chuckles]
Lightning bugs?

1284
01:07:00,691 --> 01:07:02,943
Only you.
[Sniffs]

1285
01:07:03,026 --> 01:07:05,320
[Chuckles]

1286
01:07:05,404 --> 01:07:07,990
You know, I still go
out there sometimes.

1287
01:07:10,200 --> 01:07:13,245
I see those big thunderheads
rollin' in.

1288
01:07:14,955 --> 01:07:17,332
It's like a religion.
[Chuckles]

1289
01:07:17,416 --> 01:07:20,961
I had a dream about it
the other night.

1290
01:07:23,839 --> 01:07:25,966
You ever wonder
what would have happened

1291
01:07:26,049 --> 01:07:27,968
if we hadn't have gotten
pregnant?

1292
01:07:28,010 --> 01:07:29,595
Jake...

1293
01:07:29,678 --> 01:07:31,680
Just...

1294
01:07:31,763 --> 01:07:34,850
let me get this out
before I can't.

1295
01:07:36,685 --> 01:07:38,812
I thought that baby
would be an adventure.

1296
01:07:38,895 --> 01:07:42,649
And it took me a while
to realize

1297
01:07:42,733 --> 01:07:46,486
it would have been
your only adventure.

1298
01:07:46,528 --> 01:07:49,615
I just guess Mother Nature
knew better, huh?

1299
01:07:51,783 --> 01:07:54,703
I was so ashamed...

1300
01:07:57,039 --> 01:08:01,001
...'cause I felt...

1301
01:08:01,084 --> 01:08:03,754
relieved.

1302
01:08:06,256 --> 01:08:11,762
And all of a sudden, I just...
needed a different life.

1303
01:08:14,890 --> 01:08:19,144
You done real well
for yourself.

1304
01:08:19,227 --> 01:08:21,438
I'm proud of you, Mel.

1305
01:08:23,273 --> 01:08:27,027
I'm just sorry I never danced
with you at our weddin'.

1306
01:08:31,239 --> 01:08:35,077
I'm sure this next one's
gonna go better for ya.

1307
01:08:40,374 --> 01:08:42,542
Jake, I can't do this.

1308
01:08:42,584 --> 01:08:44,169
Hey...

1309
01:08:48,006 --> 01:08:51,301
I know.

1310
01:09:17,286 --> 01:09:18,954
Go home.

1311
01:09:32,593 --> 01:09:34,052
Well, I'm just sayin',
is all.

1312
01:09:34,136 --> 01:09:35,429
I mean, I... I saw

1313
01:09:35,470 --> 01:09:37,264
the way you two
were lookin' at each other.

1314
01:09:37,306 --> 01:09:39,224
Will you just shut up
about it, Mama?!

1315
01:09:39,308 --> 01:09:41,351
I can't help
the way Jake feels about me!

1316
01:09:41,435 --> 01:09:42,978
He hasn't done
anything wrong!

1317
01:09:43,061 --> 01:09:44,938
He hasn't done anything right
either!

1318
01:09:44,980 --> 01:09:46,940
I can't believe I'm even
having this argument!

1319
01:09:46,982 --> 01:09:48,942
I'm leaving! I'm gone!

1320
01:09:48,984 --> 01:09:50,444
I'm marrying another man!

1321
01:09:50,527 --> 01:09:53,655
Yes, that's right, you get
a second chance, so please

1322
01:09:53,739 --> 01:09:54,615
don't mess it up!

1323
01:09:54,698 --> 01:09:57,326
For who?
For me or for you?

1324
01:09:57,409 --> 01:09:58,619
Don't sass me, okay?

1325
01:09:58,702 --> 01:10:01,455
Don't you dare sass me,
'cause I have put up

1326
01:10:01,496 --> 01:10:03,624
with an awful lot from you
over the years.

1327
01:10:03,665 --> 01:10:06,668
Like what?! L-Like me quitting
your precious pageants?

1328
01:10:06,752 --> 01:10:09,796
I didn't want you to
end up like me! Damn it!

1329
01:10:09,880 --> 01:10:13,508
Now, you need to stay as far
away from here as you can.

1330
01:10:13,592 --> 01:10:15,135
That boy is quicksand.

1331
01:10:15,218 --> 01:10:18,555
What's so wrong
with being you, Mama?

1332
01:10:19,806 --> 01:10:23,560
I just think that you
deserve better, that's all.

1333
01:10:23,644 --> 01:10:26,480
I know you do.

1334
01:10:29,858 --> 01:10:32,152
You always have.

1335
01:10:32,194 --> 01:10:35,238
I'll see you in New York,
all right?

1336
01:10:35,322 --> 01:10:36,657
Mm-hmm.

1337
01:10:36,698 --> 01:10:38,992
You'll like it.

1338
01:10:39,034 --> 01:10:41,119
I promise.

1339
01:10:45,540 --> 01:10:47,918
Now, don't you forget to
say goodbye to your daddy.

1340
01:10:48,001 --> 01:10:49,461
[Drumroll]

1341
01:10:49,544 --> 01:10:50,754
...Fire!
...Fire!

1342
01:10:50,837 --> 01:10:52,381
...Fire!
...Fire!

1343
01:10:52,464 --> 01:10:53,423
Fire!

1344
01:11:03,350 --> 01:11:06,687
[Cannons fire]

1345
01:11:06,728 --> 01:11:08,981
Melanie: Daddy?

1346
01:11:11,066 --> 01:11:12,526
[Firing continues]

1347
01:11:12,609 --> 01:11:14,695
Daddy?

1348
01:11:21,326 --> 01:11:22,911
Daddy!

1349
01:11:22,995 --> 01:11:25,956
Who ya lookin' for,
darlin'?

1350
01:11:26,039 --> 01:11:28,208
Earl Smooter.

1351
01:11:28,292 --> 01:11:30,877
5th Regiment?

1352
01:11:30,961 --> 01:11:32,212
[All groaning]

1353
01:11:32,296 --> 01:11:34,214
Anybody seen Earl Smooter?

1354
01:11:34,298 --> 01:11:36,550
He's about to surrender!

1355
01:11:37,509 --> 01:11:38,594
Thank you!

1356
01:11:41,722 --> 01:11:43,640
[All sigh]

1357
01:11:43,724 --> 01:11:46,685
[Tires screech, horn honks]

1358
01:11:46,768 --> 01:11:48,186
After you.

1359
01:11:57,321 --> 01:11:58,488
Afternoon.

1360
01:11:58,572 --> 01:12:01,742
...How are ya?
...Good, thanks. Yourself?

1361
01:12:01,783 --> 01:12:04,620
No complaints.

1362
01:12:04,703 --> 01:12:06,580
That's a beautiful house.

1363
01:12:06,663 --> 01:12:09,124
Sure. Yeah.

1364
01:12:09,207 --> 01:12:12,294
You, uh, you here
to see Bobby Ray?

1365
01:12:12,377 --> 01:12:15,756
Actually, I'm, uh,
hoping to surprise Melanie.

1366
01:12:15,839 --> 01:12:19,593
...Melanie?
...My fiancee.

1367
01:12:19,676 --> 01:12:22,262
You got the wrong house,
don't ya?

1368
01:12:22,346 --> 01:12:26,183
This is, uh,
the Carmichael place, isn't it?

1369
01:12:27,267 --> 01:12:29,102
Are we talkin'
about the same girl?

1370
01:12:29,144 --> 01:12:30,729
...Melanie Smooter?
...Melanie Carmichael.

1371
01:12:30,812 --> 01:12:34,608
Oh, well,
that explains it.

1372
01:12:34,691 --> 01:12:37,110
That sure does.

1373
01:12:37,152 --> 01:12:39,363
Andrew Hennings.

1374
01:12:42,074 --> 01:12:43,825
Nice meeting you, Jake.

1375
01:12:43,909 --> 01:12:46,411
[Doorbell rings]

1376
01:12:56,213 --> 01:12:58,966
Hey, Jake.

1377
01:12:59,007 --> 01:13:00,676
What's goin' on?

1378
01:13:00,759 --> 01:13:02,135
Oh, you know,

1379
01:13:02,219 --> 01:13:06,014
I'm just, uh, talkin'
to Mel's fiance here.

1380
01:13:06,098 --> 01:13:08,517
Wonder if you might know
where she is.

1381
01:13:08,600 --> 01:13:10,394
Andrew Hennings.
You must be...

1382
01:13:10,477 --> 01:13:15,440
l-I'm Bobby Ray...
her, uh, cousin?

1383
01:13:15,524 --> 01:13:19,236
I see you've already met
Jake... her, uh...

1384
01:13:19,319 --> 01:13:21,280
...Other cousin.
...[Laughs]

1385
01:13:21,363 --> 01:13:24,032
Family! God, it's great
to meet you both.

1386
01:13:24,116 --> 01:13:26,034
I think Melanie said
somethin' last night

1387
01:13:26,118 --> 01:13:27,536
about, uh, visitin'
her daddy

1388
01:13:27,619 --> 01:13:29,329
u-up at the...
up at the battlefield.

1389
01:13:29,371 --> 01:13:31,665
...The battlefield?
...You know us Southerners.

1390
01:13:31,748 --> 01:13:33,333
I mean, the minute
the Confederacy died,

1391
01:13:33,417 --> 01:13:34,710
it became a moral issue.

1392
01:13:34,793 --> 01:13:39,006
Come on, I'll, uh, I'll
give you a ride up there.

1393
01:13:39,089 --> 01:13:42,009
That's great. Thank you.
All right. Nice meeting you.

1394
01:13:44,386 --> 01:13:49,516
# What this world needs
is a few more rednecks #

1395
01:13:49,558 --> 01:13:51,435
# So people ain't afraid
to take a stand #

1396
01:13:51,518 --> 01:13:55,522
So, who's...
Melanie... Smooter?

1397
01:13:55,606 --> 01:13:57,816
Local hero around here.

1398
01:13:57,899 --> 01:13:59,693
Why is that?

1399
01:13:59,735 --> 01:14:01,028
She blew up the bank.

1400
01:14:01,111 --> 01:14:03,363
And that made her a hero?

1401
01:14:03,447 --> 01:14:07,576
Well, notorious, anyway.
She was 10.

1402
01:14:07,659 --> 01:14:08,910
Oh.

1403
01:14:08,994 --> 01:14:13,206
Fortunately, nobody was hurt...
except, maybe, the cat.

1404
01:14:13,248 --> 01:14:15,417
What cat?

1405
01:14:15,500 --> 01:14:18,003
The one with the dynamite
on its back.

1406
01:14:18,086 --> 01:14:20,881
She blew up a cat?

1407
01:14:20,964 --> 01:14:23,300
...He was scheduled to die.
...From dynamite?

1408
01:14:23,383 --> 01:14:25,886
The vet said it had cancer,

1409
01:14:25,969 --> 01:14:28,931
so Eldon thought it'd be put
in one of those chambers,

1410
01:14:29,014 --> 01:14:31,683
you know, the ones
that suck their lungs out.

1411
01:14:31,767 --> 01:14:34,561
Little Mel, she couldn't bear
the thought of that.

1412
01:14:34,645 --> 01:14:37,064
She, uh, she wanted
somethin' more humane.

1413
01:14:37,147 --> 01:14:39,066
Yeah, sure.

1414
01:14:39,107 --> 01:14:42,277
So, they were doing some
blastin' out by the new highway.

1415
01:14:42,361 --> 01:14:45,447
So, we, uh, we took
old Fuzz up there,

1416
01:14:45,530 --> 01:14:46,907
taped him up.

1417
01:14:46,949 --> 01:14:50,452
Used about 30 feet of fuse
just to be on the safe side,

1418
01:14:50,535 --> 01:14:52,287
said our prayers,
and ran like hell.

1419
01:14:52,371 --> 01:14:54,247
Of course.

1420
01:14:54,331 --> 01:14:56,249
So, there we were,
sittin' in Virgie's Diner,

1421
01:14:56,291 --> 01:14:58,835
feelin' pretty blue.

1422
01:14:58,919 --> 01:15:00,921
When Mel looks up and sees
that damn cat,

1423
01:15:01,004 --> 01:15:04,132
trottin' down the road,
searchin' for Eldon.

1424
01:15:04,216 --> 01:15:06,593
No shit.

1425
01:15:06,635 --> 01:15:08,428
Yeah, and we
would have caught him, too,

1426
01:15:08,470 --> 01:15:11,682
but once that fuse hit his tail,
boom, he took off like a shot.

1427
01:15:11,765 --> 01:15:13,141
And into the bank.

1428
01:15:13,225 --> 01:15:15,769
Well... the theory is,

1429
01:15:15,852 --> 01:15:17,854
he probably wriggled loose
from the explosive.

1430
01:15:17,938 --> 01:15:21,316
'Cause, uh, people still
see him from time to time,

1431
01:15:21,400 --> 01:15:23,110
scorched tail and all.

1432
01:15:23,151 --> 01:15:26,446
He's a little skittish
around humans.

1433
01:15:26,488 --> 01:15:28,949
That's quite a story.

1434
01:15:28,991 --> 01:15:31,118
She was quite a girl.

1435
01:15:31,159 --> 01:15:34,037
# A little less talk
and a little more action #

1436
01:15:34,121 --> 01:15:36,039
Whatever happened to her?

1437
01:15:36,123 --> 01:15:37,457
# And a few more rednecks... #

1438
01:15:37,499 --> 01:15:40,752
Oh, you know...
wound up pregnant,

1439
01:15:40,836 --> 01:15:44,840
married some loser
right out of high school.

1440
01:15:44,923 --> 01:15:50,304
[Trumpet playing "Taps"]

1441
01:16:03,609 --> 01:16:04,943
["Taps" ends]

1442
01:16:05,027 --> 01:16:08,030
[Whistling,
cheers and applause]

1443
01:16:18,290 --> 01:16:20,751
Are you surprised?

1444
01:16:24,212 --> 01:16:26,048
What are you doing here?

1445
01:16:26,131 --> 01:16:28,258
Well, I came to deliver
your fiance.

1446
01:16:28,342 --> 01:16:29,593
I think
she was talking to me.

1447
01:16:29,676 --> 01:16:30,719
Jake...

1448
01:16:30,802 --> 01:16:32,429
Must be exhaustin'.

1449
01:16:32,512 --> 01:16:33,430
...What?
...What?

1450
01:16:33,513 --> 01:16:34,973
Livin' a lie.

1451
01:16:35,057 --> 01:16:36,266
What's he talking about?

1452
01:16:37,768 --> 01:16:40,729
You and I are in love
with two different people.

1453
01:16:46,652 --> 01:16:49,112
Is he a second cousin?

1454
01:16:50,238 --> 01:16:52,032
He's my husband.

1455
01:16:52,074 --> 01:16:53,241
Your what?

1456
01:16:53,325 --> 01:16:54,326
I mean my ex-husband.

1457
01:16:54,409 --> 01:16:55,869
You married your cousin?!

1458
01:16:55,953 --> 01:16:58,705
No, I came down here
to finalize my divorce.

1459
01:16:58,747 --> 01:17:01,249
Hey, darlin',
thought that was you.

1460
01:17:03,835 --> 01:17:05,545
Must be your new someone.

1461
01:17:07,130 --> 01:17:09,049
Earl Smooter...
glad to meet ya.

1462
01:17:12,928 --> 01:17:14,596
Melanie Smooter.

1463
01:17:17,432 --> 01:17:18,392
Andrew, wait.

1464
01:17:18,475 --> 01:17:20,060
Wait!

1465
01:17:20,143 --> 01:17:23,063
Andrew! Wait!

1466
01:17:23,146 --> 01:17:24,064
I just...

1467
01:17:24,147 --> 01:17:25,274
Please.

1468
01:17:25,357 --> 01:17:27,234
Let me try
and explain myself!

1469
01:17:27,276 --> 01:17:29,278
You don't understand!

1470
01:17:29,319 --> 01:17:31,738
This is not
who I am anymore!

1471
01:17:31,780 --> 01:17:33,782
Look, I don't know who you are
or what else you lied about,

1472
01:17:33,865 --> 01:17:35,284
but I know one thing...

1473
01:17:35,367 --> 01:17:38,996
there is a Lear Jet
in Mobile, and I am on it.

1474
01:17:41,039 --> 01:17:43,333
[Sighs]

1475
01:17:59,558 --> 01:18:00,934
I know you're thinkin'

1476
01:18:01,018 --> 01:18:03,770
I spoiled things good
this time.

1477
01:18:03,812 --> 01:18:07,524
Oh, hon, don't go accusin' me
of thinkin'.

1478
01:18:07,608 --> 01:18:10,736
I ain't done
anything of the sort.

1479
01:18:10,819 --> 01:18:13,780
Anyway, spoiled's in the eye
of the beholder...

1480
01:18:15,449 --> 01:18:16,908
...like these plums here.

1481
01:18:16,992 --> 01:18:20,787
Some people might
call them "spoiled"...

1482
01:18:20,829 --> 01:18:25,125
but I think that, um,
these almost-ruined ones

1483
01:18:25,167 --> 01:18:28,128
sometimes make
the sweetest jam.

1484
01:18:30,130 --> 01:18:32,007
Do you need any help?

1485
01:18:34,134 --> 01:18:35,719
It was kind of fun,

1486
01:18:35,802 --> 01:18:38,055
seeing Daddy up there,
surrendering.

1487
01:18:38,138 --> 01:18:40,098
Yeah.

1488
01:18:40,182 --> 01:18:42,976
He sure does have
a flair for the dramatic.

1489
01:18:43,018 --> 01:18:46,146
You certainly don't get it
from my side of the family.

1490
01:18:48,273 --> 01:18:50,108
Hey, y'all.

1491
01:18:50,192 --> 01:18:52,486
Look who I found
walkin' down l-58.

1492
01:18:52,569 --> 01:18:54,363
Hi.

1493
01:18:54,446 --> 01:18:57,282
Hi.

1494
01:18:59,201 --> 01:19:02,579
I thought you'd be
halfway to New York by now.

